The chairman of Inter-Party Advisory Committee (IPAC) in Lagos State, Mobolaji Olusegun, has hailed Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu for considering the needs and aspiration of Lagosians before implementating policies and programmes. He congratulated the governor for the approval and issuance of Certificate of Clearance for two additional state universities in the state Olusegun said: We commend the speaker of the house and the lawmakers for their cooperation and collective effort towards this great achievement. “Quality Education is one of the major factor and key element of growth and stability for any society or nation, and Lagos state government under the leadership of governor Sanw-Olu Is taking a good step in the right direction to build a sane and responsible society through quality education. Olusegun of *Young Progressives Party (YPP)*, who spoke in Lagos, said, the best thing that can happen to make this effort what its while, is to make adequate provision of good facilities, infrastructure and conducive learning environment for the students. He added:”We will also advice that good maintenance system and culture be adopted and put in place for continuity. “It is one thing to provide quality education, it is another thing to have a job after school. in view of this, it will be more well appreciated that more job opportunities are created for existing graduates and provisions made for coming ones.”